# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Use this page during an active DR event to choose the fastest safe recovery path.

## DR objective

Restore PostgreSQL data to UK South as fast as possible with auditable steps.

## Decision guide

1. If the Azure DevOps restore pipeline is available and credentials are working, use [Restore to UK South using Automation (CNP and CPP)](restore-to-uksouth-automation.html).
2. If Azure DevOps is unavailable, service connection access is blocked, or automation fails repeatedly at stage startup, use [Restore to UK South using Azure Portal (Manual)](restore-to-uksouth-portal.html).
3. If vault restore has already completed but DB replay failed, re-run only the DB phase using `restoreMode=database-only` and the existing container, _note if any data has been loaded then a clean up is required to mitigate duplicate data in `database-only` mode._

## Critical checks before pressing restore

- Confirm source environment and source server naming.
  - You will need the source Postgresql instance name and resource group for the pipeline inputs
- Confirm restore point (latest or explicit point-in-time).
  - You can choose to restore the latest available backup or a specific point in time using the `recoveryPointId`
- Confirm restore storage and SKU settings (optional)
  - The automation will create a new Postgresql instance matching the source but depending on the criticality of the server higher storage and SKU settings can speed up restore times.

